# Chart Recall Consumption

## Finish line

The ADR functional bar, operationalized on the consumption side: every agent
context (claude/codex/pi, fleet-wide) and every human surface (paper, phone,
attached herdr sessions) uses the distilled layer BY DEFAULT — push
(session-start briefing carries recent distilled work), pull (one hybrid
recall surface answering "what did we do/decide about X"), and editorial
(the morning edition mines observations for open loops and closures) — with
recall quality measured, not vibed. Reached when an agent on any machine
wakes already knowing the fleet's recent work, and the paper's morning
edition cites observation pages as sources.

Charter condition (Joel, 2026-07-13): "for the consumption side if we are
happy with ingest" — the write loop (observer v1.3) is treated as good
enough; ingest changes belong to the observational-memory map, not here.

## Notes

- **Adjacency — do not duplicate**: the
  [observational-memory map](../observational-memory/observational-memory-brief.svx) owns
  the WRITE loop, page quality, and the reflector/temporal gradient
  (weekly compaction, monthly promotion). This map consumes whatever that
  loop produces. Two open tickets RE-PARENTED here as consumption surfaces:
  [Productionize qmd](./build-qmd-knowledge-projection.svx) (pull) and
  [Observations as Prime Bugle Source](./build-observations-bugle-source.svx)
  (editorial).
- **Consumption inventory (live today, receipts from 2026-07-12/13)**:
  `joelclaw sessions search` defaults to the observations collection
  (gists + canonical URLs + sensitive labels); voice `recall_work`
  (caller-gated); non-sensitive pages render at brain.joelclaw.com with a
  daily index; qmd adopted (509 svx, hybrid receipts) but unwired.
- **The gap is push**: everything live is pull — agents must think to ask.
  The briefing is the multiplier.
- **Privacy inherited**: sensitive = recallable locally, never rendered,
  never spoken to unverified callers, never in any surface that leaves the
  tailnet. The qmd caller-boundary caveat gates MCP exposure.
- **Skills**: `/skill:grill-master`, `/skill:session-search`,
  `/skill:brain-first-workflow`, `/skill:joel-writing-style`.

## Decision ledger

- [Bench Recall Quality](./bench-recall-quality.svx) — consumption leg shipped with five held-out canonical-page queries outside Brain roots; July baseline: sessions-search 1/5 (MRR 0.20), qmd hybrid 3/5 (MRR 0.34), paper index 0/5 (MRR 0.00). The zeroes stay visible as coverage failures.

- [Bench Recall Quality (brainbench consumption leg)](./bench-recall-quality.svx) — baseline shipped: known-answer fixtures scored across all three pull surfaces; rerun cadence as corpus grows.

## Not yet specified

- Cross-machine pull: sessions-search rides central Typesense (works
  fleet-wide) but qmd's index is flagg-local — what do blaine agents get,
  and is it one shared index or per-machine?
- Consumption telemetry: ClickHouse events for which recalls get used —
  eventual ranking signal for the reflector (feeds back to the other map).
- Codex-specific consumption (its capture is still broken; consuming
  before contributing is odd — may hang on fix-codex-capture-delivery).
- "Ask the paper" — conversational recall UI on brain.joelclaw.com itself
  (toolbar territory; waits for the toolbar ticket).

## Out of scope

- Write-loop/ingest changes, reflector policy, page quality — the
  observational-memory map owns all of it.
- Public or shared access to any recall surface.
